    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You have learned a trick that makes your spellcasting more flexible.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Spell Mastery, wizard level 1st.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>When you prepare your spells each day, you can choose to keep a number of spell slots equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1) flexibly prepared. Instead of preparing a single spell within each of these slots, you can partially prepare two spells. Anytime after you prepare these flexible slots, you can spend a full-round action to finalize one slot, choosing one of the two spells to be finished and fully prepared in that slot.",
